/ref>\n:<sup>{{note|Relocated|[a]}}</sup> The game between LSU and BYU was originally scheduled to take place at [[NRG Stadium]] in [[Houston|Houston, Texas]].  However, due to massive flooding caused by [[Hurricane Harvey]] in the Houston area, school and game officials decided to relocate the game to New Orleans.<ref>https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2017/8/27/16210992/hurricane-harvey-lsu-byu-game-houston-2017</ref>\n\n==Rankings==\n{{Further|2017 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings}}\n{{NCAA Division I FBS CFP ranking movements\n| year            = {{2017}}\n| finalpollweek   = 15\n| cfpfirstweek    = 9\n| AP_pre          = 13\n| coaches_pre     = 12\n| AP_1            = 12\n| coaches_1       = 12\n| AP_2            = 12\n| coaches_2       = 11\n| AP_3            = 25\n| coaches_3       = 23\n| AP_4            = 25\n| coaches_4       = 22\n| AP_5            = NR\n| coaches_5       = NR\n| AP_6            = RV\n| coaches_6       = RV\n| AP_7            = 24\n| coaches_7       = 25\n| AP_8            = 23\n| coaches_8       = 23\n| AP_9            = 23\n| coaches_9       = 23\n| cfp_9           = NR\n| AP_10           = 19\n| coaches_10      = 20\n| cfp_10          = 19\n| AP_11           = RV\n| coaches_11      = 25\n| cfp_11          = 24\n| AP_12           = 21\n| coaches_12      = 21\n| cfp_12          = 20\n| AP_13           = 19\n| coaches_13      = 18\n| cfp_13          = 18\n| AP_14           = 16\n| coaches_14      = 14\n| cfp_14          = 17\n| AP_15           = 18\n| coaches_15      = 18\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{LSU Tigers football navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2017 LSU Tigers Football Team}}\n[[Category:2017 Southeastern Conference football season|LSU]]\n[[Category:LSU Tigers football seasons]]\n[[Category:2017 in sports in Louisiana|LSU Tigers f]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year= 2017\n  |team= LSU Tigers\n  |sport= football\n  |image= Louisiana State University (block logo).svg\n  |image_size= 125px\n  |conference= Southeastern Conference\n  |short_conf= SEC\n  |division= Western Division\n  |CoachRank= 18\n  |APRank= 18\n  |CFPRank=\n  |record = 9\u20134\n  |conf_record = 6\u20132\n  |head_coach= [[Ed Orgeron]]\n  |hc_year=1st full year as HC; 2nd overall\n  |off_coach= [[Matt Canada]]\n  |oc_year = 1st\n  |cooff_coach2 = \n  |cooc2_year = \n  |off_scheme= Multiple\n  |def_coach= [[Dave Aranda]]\n  |dc_year= 2nd\n  |def_scheme= [[3-4 defense|3\u20134]]\n  |stadium= [[Tiger Stadium (LSU)|Tiger Stadium]] (Capacity: 102,321)\n  |champion=\n  |bowl= [[2018 Citrus Bowl|Citrus Bowl]]\n  |bowl_result= L, 17\u201321 vs. [[2017 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team|Notre Dame]] \n}}\n{{2017 SEC football standings}}\nThe '''2017 LSU Tigers football team''' represented [[Louisiana State University]] in the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Tigers played their home games at [[Tiger Stadium (LSU)|Tiger Stadium]] in [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]] and competed in the Western Division of the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC). They were led by first-year head coach [[Ed Orgeron]] after he led the Tigers as interim head coach for the final eight games of 2016. They finished the season 9\u20134, 6\u20132 in SEC play to finish in third place in the Western Division. They were invited to the [[2018 Citrus Bowl|Citrus Bowl]] where they lost to [[2017 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team|Notre Dame]].\n\nThe Tigers equaled an [[NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision|FBS]] record by committing only eight turnovers during the season, becoming the sixth FBS team to do so. The record would fall [[2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season|the next season]] to [[2018 Georgia Southern Eagles football team|Georgia Southern]], which had only five turnovers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/recap?gameId=401032056 |title=Georgia Southern tops Eastern Michigan 23-21 on Bass' FG |agency=Associated Press |website=ESPN.com |date=December 15, 2018 |accessdate=December 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Recruiting==\n===Position key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[Running back|Back]]\n|'''B'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Center (American football)|Center]]\n|'''C'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Cornerback]]\n|'''CB'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Defensive back]]\n|'''DB'''\n|-\n|[[Defensive end]]\n|'''DE'''\n|[[Defensive lineman]]\n|'''DL'''\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|'''DT'''\n|[[End (American football)|End]]\n|'''E'''\n|-\n|[[Fullback (American football)|Fullback]]\n|'''FB'''\n|[[Guard (American football)|Guard]]\n|'''G'''\n|[[Halfback (American football)|Halfback]]\n|'''HB'''\n|[[Placekicker|Kicker]]\n|'''K'''\n|-\n|[[Kickoff returner]]\n|'''KR'''\n|[[Offensive tackle]]\n|'''OT'''\n|[[Lineman (American football)|Offensive lineman]]\n|'''OL'''\n|[[Linebacker]]\n|'''LB'''\n|-\n|[[Long snapper]]\n|'''LS'''\n|[[Punter (American football)|Punter]]\n|'''P'''\n|[[Punt returner]]\n|'''PR'''\n|[[Quarterback]]\n|'''QB'''\n|-\n|[[Running back]]\n|'''RB'''\n|[[Safety (American and Canadian football position)|Safety]]\n|'''S'''\n|[[Tight end]]\n|'''TE'''\n|[[Wide receiver]]\n|'''WR'''\n|}\n\n===Recruits===\n\nThe Tigers signed a total of 23 recruits.\n\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=yes|year=2017}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Tyler Shelvin\n| position = DT\n| hometown = [[Crowley, Louisiana]]\n| highschool = [[Notre Dame High School (Crowley, Louisiana)|Notre Dame HS]]\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 3\n| weight = 360\n| commitdate = March 11, 2015\n| scout stars  = 4\n| rivals stars = 5\n| 247 stars = 4\n| espn stars = 4\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = [[Clyde Edwards-Helaire]]\n| position = RB\n| hometown = [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana]]\n| highschool = [[Catholic High School (Baton Rouge, Louisiana)|Catholic HS]]\n| feet   = 5\n| inches = 7\n| weight = 