er/Player|num=89|class=JR|first=Trey|last=Gallman|pos=LS}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=94|class=FR|first=Brandon|last=McQuen|pos=K}}\n\n}}\n{{American football roster/Footer|roster_url=http://www.lsusports.net/SportSelect.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5200&SPID=2164&SPSID=27812&KEY=&Q_SEASON=2017|accessdate=10/25/18\n\n|head_coach=\n*[[Ed Orgeron]]\n|asst_coach=\n*[[Matt Canada]] \u2013 ''Offensive Coordinator''\n*[[Dave Aranda]] \u2013 ''Associate Head Coach/Defensive Coordinator''\n*Tommie Robinson \u2013 ''Assistant Head Coach/Running Backs/Recruiting Coordinator''\n*[[Mickey Joseph]] \u2013 ''Wide Receivers''\n*[[Steve Ensminger]] \u2013 ''Tight Ends''\n*[[Pete Jenkins]] \u2013 ''Defensive Line''\n*[[Jeff Grimes]] \u2013 ''Offensive Line/Running Game Coordinator''\n*Dennis Johnson \u2013 ''Outside Linebackers''\n*[[Corey Raymond]] \u2013 ''Defensive Backs''\n*Tommy Moffitt \u2013 ''Assistant Athletic Director/Strength and Conditioning''\n*Dr. Sam Nader \u2013 ''Assistant Athletic Director - Football\n*Sharon Lewis \u2013 ''Assistant Athletic Director/Football Recruiting and Alumni Relations''\n*Austin Thomas \u2013 ''General Manager''\n}}\n\n==Schedule==\nLSU announced its 2017 football schedule on September 13, 2016. The 2017 schedule consisted of 6 home, 5 away and 1 neutral site game in the regular season. The Tigers hosted SEC foes [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]], [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]], and [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]], and traveled to [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]], [[Florida Gators football|Florida]], [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]], [[Ole Miss Rebels football|Ole Miss]], and [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]].<ref name=\"LSU17\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.lsusports.net/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=27815&SPID=2164&DB_LANG=C&DB_OEM_ID=5200&ATCLID=211169571|title=Save the Dates! 2017 Football Schedule Announced |publisher=Louisiana State University Department of Athletics|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=January 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe Tigers hosted three of the four non-conference opponents, [[Chattanooga Mocs football|Chattanooga]] from the [[NCAA Division I#Football Championship Subdivision|FCS]] [[Southern Conference]], [[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse]] from the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] and [[Troy Trojans football|Troy]] from the [[Sun Belt Conference]] and traveled to [[New Orleans]] to for a neutral site matchup against [[NCAA Division I FBS independent schools|independent]] [[BYU Cougars football|BYU]].\n{{-}}\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2017\n| poll = [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 2\n| time = 8:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| neutral = y\n| rank = 13\n| opponent = [[2017 BYU Cougars football team|BYU]]\n| gamename = [[Texas Kickoff]]\n| site_stadium = [[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]]\n| site_cityst = [[New Orleans|New Orleans, LA]]{{ref|Relocated|[a]}}\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football Saturday Primetime|ESPN]]\n| score = 27\u20130\n| attend = 53,826\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 9\n| time = 6:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[2017 Chattanooga Mocs football team|Chattanooga]]\n| site_stadium = [[Tiger Stadium (LSU)|Tiger Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Baton Rouge, Louisiana|Baton Rouge, LA]]\n| tv = [[SEC Network|SECN]]\n| score = 45\u201310\n| attend = 97,289\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 16\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[2017 Mississippi State Bulldogs football team|Mississippi State]]\n| gamename = [[LSU\u2013Mississippi State football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| site_stadium = [[Davis Wade Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Starkville, Mississippi|Starkville, MS]]\n| tv = ESPN\n| score = 7\u201337\n| attend = 60,596\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 23\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n